Dr Naledi Pandor says South Africa should wait for the President to announce his Cabinet. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Higher Education Minister, Naledi Pandor is neither denying nor confirming if she's been offered the position of deputy president. "Any appoint to the Cabinet is the prerogative of the president and this is all just a wild speculation, so let's wait on the president to announce his Cabinet," Pandor said. READ: Malema: 'I won't serve in a Cabinet through the back door' Calls have been mounting for South Africa to have a female deputy president. The names of Minister in the Presidency, Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma and Pandor have been bandied about as possible replacements. WATCH: President Cyril Ramaphosa's inauguration On Wednesday, ANC deputy president David Mabuza, asked for his swearing in as an MP to be postponed. He wants to first address allegations against him by the party's integrity commission. President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to announce his new Cabinet on Sunday. 